Time is absolutely being removed from the audio files. There is so
much more than just listening to the files, you have too look. You
have to train your eyes as well as your ears to make any sort of
judgment. The second I load some of these files, before I listen, I
see problems. I know the site isn&#39;t set up to really leave comments on
files with the file but something should be included in the name or
something. Without it, it is not true representation of what the file
is or what has happened between the capture and the post. We listen
and think &quot;Wow! Great catch&quot; but we really do not know. 

Are you starting the scan on your 3 469&#39;s at different frequencies?
What is the ratio being mixed? Is it equal between the three? 

I believe that Mark and Debbie Constantino (sp)of Nevada use water
almost exclusively for their recordings. I have found that method to
be difficult in hearing the results. Are you feeling that those
communications are from spirits or earthbounds and what makes you feel
that way?

I&#39;ve recently started analyzing a 40 min 469 session. The results are
scary. I&#39;d say at this point, and I&#39;m only 1/2 way through, 90% of the
communication is negative in nature and mentions many supposed Demonic
names. The layers of voices are, in many cases, multiple. Often, the
listener hears very little of what is actually said. The voices can be
mocking or downright crude. I have not yet formed an opinion fully but
it would seem to me that these models are easy devices for lower level
entities to figure out how to use. I can not speak of the attitudes or
fears of those investigators present although at times, their voices
are a bit shaky. 

Babs

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Ratka &lt;warrior18eii@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Very good observation Babs. Let me say that you have many friends
and associates here just for the simple fact that you have an interest
in ITC, are a researcher and a complex thinker. I think we have shown
in the past that we can have a disagreement and still remain friends.
You make a lot of good points in your post and I would like to know
who removes time from their recordings. I have never removed time from
my recordings and see no reason why anyone else would without saying
so in an accompanied post.
&gt; 
&gt; I have limited experience with the 12-469&#39;s as a single piece of
equipment. I have arranged mine per Mike&#39;s, &quot;Spiricomp&quot; design. I have
3, 12-469&#39;s feeding a four channel mixer, which goes into a laptop
running DC6 with Soundsoap 2. Mine scan equally spaced on the FM band.
I have had pretty good results until recently.
&gt; 
&gt; At first the messages were pretty clear but I had a feeling I was
getting a different group than I normally have for the last few years.
When I would ask about my friends on the other side they would tell me
they will look for them. Well about 2 weeks ago the 12-469 arrangement
started generating a lot of interference and feedback. I started
hearing radio static voices as I use to get with shortwave. Not voice
fragments but voices made of static (metallic and robotic). They were
breaking through the sweeping. I had a feeling someone else was trying
to force their way through. Finally the interference got so bad I was
forced to revert back to a simpler method I used before, which is
using fan noise. One of the first messages to come across was from a
familiar voice telling me and I quote, &quot;your method sucks&quot;. I have not
used the 12-469&#39;s since because of the clear messages I have been
getting using water and fan noise. That does not mean I have given up
&gt;  on the 12-469&#39;s but I won&#39;t use them again until I am persuaded to
by my friends on the otherside that they are willing to use and adapt
to it. To my knowledge only Misty, Laura and myself use water for
recording.
&gt; 
&gt; Regards,
&gt; 
&gt; Frank R.
